Looking at this board, I would say that mages are by and large doing pretty well.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Rthen</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> has his own board, dedicated to his point of view that mage suck: <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://rthen2001.proboards4.com/index.cgi">Rthen's Mage Board</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->.  The main board has 16 topics, and 77 posts, most of which are by three users, including <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Rthen</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  Obviously, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Rthen</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is being suppressed by <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Mage Compendium</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and the enormous groundswell of activity there supports his contention that the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;vast majority&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> of mages are unhappy.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Rthen</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is pretty unhappy, that's for sure.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Rthen:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  The difference between a modestly equipped Warrior and an uber warrior is far less then a modestly equipped Mage and an uber mage.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->This is most patently absurd statement in the lot.  While there may not be minor version of BoBC and SoA, they matter less to mages then really good equipment matters to melees.  By and large, mage equipment grants us easier access to our innate abilities, such as mana free spells we can already cast, or increased mana regeneration so we cast more spells sooner.  But melee equipment dramatically effects their survival in combat <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> (their primary function)</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, gives the access to procs and right click effects they are completely outside their class abilities, and crank up their damage output in a steady and completely predictable way <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> (i.e. damage/delay)</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Rthen:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  All of the &quot;uber&quot; mages have all of the same equipment...<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->I guess I'm uber, or demi-uber or something, but I lack epic, regen, and flowing thought, yet I do not suffer greatly.  Jeeze, with serial pet reclamation, who the hell needs flowing thought?  This is available to <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>any</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> 49+ mage with malachite.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> My point is very few mages are indeed amoung the best damage dealers or able to solo very well.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->And this is demonstrably false.  The problem here, really, is that <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Rthen</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> does not know how to play his magician very well.  Rather than acknowledge this shortcoming, he instead blames others.  He blames <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Verant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> for doing a poor job of designing the class, and he blames <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;uber&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> mages, for having all the toys he wants, and worse: for being better mages than he is.  The <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;poverty&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is not the of the mage class, but of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Rthen</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Naladini:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Should there be another, more easily attainable version that casts a level 29-34 nuke with a 10 second cast time? Yes.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Seems reasonable to me, and lower and mid-level right click nukes has been a strong demand of some wizards for class balance for quite some time.  It is true that the middle levels are empty of significant gear.  It is also true that gear matters less for mages generally.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Bazazu:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  I can *just barely* quad toilers 100% naked.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Excellent to hear that!  Of course, it would be foolish for mages to ignore their summoned gear.  I was able to solo dark blues nekkid for a couple hours, trying to kill placeholders so I could get at the tougher creatures, and downtime was not much of an issue.<br>
<br>
Point is, mages do not suck, they do pretty well, and are less dependent on equipment than other classes.  There is so much potential in our spell books alone, that anything else is icing on the cake.  Flowing Thought and runes, while nice, are not necessary, neither are right-click nukes.<br>
